  <h1>Page Shell</h1>
  <p class="lead">Base HTML5 document structure with header, main content area, and footer. The foundation for every page.</p>

  <section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>This snippet provides a complete HTML5 page structure with semantic landmarks. It includes the essential document setup: DOCTYPE, meta tags, CSS imports, and the basic page layout grid.</p>
      <p><strong>Key features:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Semantic HTML5 structure (header, main, footer)</li>
        <li>CSS Grid for sticky footer layout</li>
        <li>Responsive navigation with pill styling</li>
        <li>Preconnect hints for performance</li>
        <li>Module script loading for JavaScript</li>
      </ul>
    </layout-text>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Live Example</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>A minimal page with header navigation, main content area, and footer.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/snippets/demos/page-shell.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/page-shell"
      title="Page Shell"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Source Code</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Copy this as your starting point for any new page.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <code-block language="html" label="page-shell.html">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html lang="en"&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
  &lt;meta charset="UTF-8"&gt;
  &lt;meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"&gt;
  &lt;title&gt;Page Title - Site Name&lt;/title&gt;

  &lt;!-- Preconnect for performance --&gt;
  &lt;link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" crossorigin&gt;

  &lt;!-- CSS --&gt;
  &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="/src/main.css"&gt;

  &lt;!-- Optional: Page-specific styles --&gt;
  &lt;style&gt;
    /* Page-specific overrides go here */
  &lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
  &lt;header&gt;
    &lt;a href="/" class="logo"&gt;Site Name&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;nav class="horizontal pills" aria-label="Main navigation"&gt;
      &lt;ul&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/"&gt;Home&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/about/"&gt;About&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/contact/"&gt;Contact&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;/ul&gt;
    &lt;/nav&gt;
  &lt;/header&gt;

  &lt;main&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt;Page Title&lt;/h1&gt;
    &lt;!-- Main content here --&gt;
  &lt;/main&gt;

  &lt;footer&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;&amp;copy; 2024 Site Name. All rights reserved.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/footer&gt;

  &lt;!-- JavaScript --&gt;
  &lt;script type="module" src="/src/main.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Structure Breakdown</h2>

    <h3>Document Head</h3>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Essential meta tags and resource loading:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><code>&lt;meta charset="UTF-8"&gt;</code> - Character encoding</li>
        <li><code>&lt;meta name="viewport"&gt;</code> - Responsive viewport settings</li>
        <li><code>&lt;link rel="preconnect"&gt;</code> - Performance optimization for external resources</li>
        <li><code>&lt;link rel="stylesheet"&gt;</code> - Main CSS file</li>
      </ul>
    </layout-text>

    <h3>Header</h3>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Site branding and primary navigation:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Logo/site name links to homepage</li>
        <li>Navigation uses <code>nav.horizontal.pills</code> pattern</li>
        <li><code>aria-label</code> identifies the navigation purpose</li>
      </ul>
    </layout-text>

    <h3>Main</h3>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Primary content area. The <code>&lt;main&gt;</code> element:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Should contain only one per page</li>
        <li>Identifies the main content for assistive technology</li>
        <li>Skip links can target this element</li>
      </ul>
    </layout-text>

    <h3>Footer</h3>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Site-wide footer content:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Copyright and legal information</li>
        <li>Secondary navigation links (optional)</li>
        <li>Contact information (optional)</li>
      </ul>
    </layout-text>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Usage Notes</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Language:</strong> Always set <code>lang</code> attribute on <code>&lt;html&gt;</code> for accessibility</li>
        <li><strong>Title:</strong> Use format "Page Title - Site Name" for browser tabs and bookmarks</li>
        <li><strong>Scripts:</strong> Use <code>type="module"</code> for modern JavaScript with ES modules</li>
        <li><strong>Sticky footer:</strong> Use CSS Grid with <code>grid-template-rows: auto 1fr auto</code> and <code>min-height: 100vh</code></li>
      </ul>
    </layout-text>
  </section>

